        <custodhist id="ref9">
            <head>Custodial History</head>
            <p>The records of the President's Office from 1908 to 1935 were stored in Gulley Hall until about 1960, when they were relocated to the attic of Beach Hall. In 1968 they were brought to the Special Collections Department.</p>
        </custodhist>
        <prefercite id="ref10">
            <head>Preferred Citation</head>
            <p>[Item description, #:#], University of Connecticut, President's Office Records [Charles B. Gentry, 1928-1929]. 
                <corpname>Archives &amp; Special Collections at the Thomas J. Dodd Research Center</corpname>, 
